                                                                                                                                   LOOSE CHANGE

               
	 Beginning February 1, existing and new mutual fund investors wishing to invest Rs 50,000 or more will have to comply with the Know Your Customer (KYC) norms. This is subsequent to guidelines issued by Sebi and the Association of Mutual Funds in India relating to the requirements of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002. Investors will have to submit the KYC form along with PAN card details, proof of identity, proof of address and a passport-size photograph at designated centres of mutual funds.
              
	 Birla Sun Life Insurance Company takes 3.7 days on an average to settle a claim, according a survey conducted by the US-based LOMA International. The survey was conducted across 17 participants from Asia, including five from India. An analysis of the type of claims received revealed that over 50 per cent of the claims are on account of death because of accident and cardiac ailments. 
              
	 ING Vysya Life Insurance Company has launched ING Guaranteed Growth Plan, a unit-linked insurance plan that guarantees a 5 per cent return on the premium invested. This is the first Ulip that offers a guaranteed return. The market-linked insurance plan offers a choice of policy term of either 10 or 15 years. 
                                                              
